"title": "4975: week",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "4975",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The pattern of weeks provides a useful framework for marking time in agricultural and religious life.  The story of creation is described in terms of seven days and illustrates a cycle of work and rest.  Feasts and other rituals last for a certain number of weeks.</p>\n<h2>The seven days of creation</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:1-Gen2:3\">GEN 2:1–2:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen1:5\">GEN 1:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen1:8\">GEN 1:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen1:13\">GEN 1:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen1:19\">GEN 1:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen1:23\">GEN 1:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen1:31\">GEN 1:31</a></p>\n<h2>The Sabbath-rest</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut5:12-Deut5:14\">DEU 5:12–5:14</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:8-Exod20:11\">EXO 20:8–20:11</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:21\">EXO 34:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod35:2\">EXO 35:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb4:3-Heb4:4\">HEB 4:3–4:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb4:8-Heb4:10\">HEB 4:8–4:10</a></p>\n<h2>Seven-day intervals or periods</h2>\n<h3>After building the ark Noah had seven days' notice of the flood</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen7:4\">GEN 7:4</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Noah sent out the dove at seven-day intervals</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen8:8-Gen8:12\">GEN 8:8–8:12</a></p>\n<h3>Marching round Jericho</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:30\">HEB 11:30</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh6:12-Josh6:15\">JOS 6:12–6:15</a></p>\n<h3>Other examples of seven-day intervals or periods</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod7:25\">EXO 7:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:30\">EXO 29:30</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam10:8\">1SA 10:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam11:3\">1SA 11:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam13:8\">1SA 13:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs20:29\">1KI 20:29</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr9:25\">1CH 9:25</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:6\">ACT 20:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts21:4\">ACT 21:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts28:14\">ACT 28:14</a></p>\n<h2>Rituals lasting seven days</h2>\n<h3>Menstrual impurity</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev15:19\">LEV 15:19</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Initial period of uncleanness after childbirth</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev12:1-Lev12:2\">LEV 12:1–12:2</a></strong> <em>This would be fourteen days if the child were a girl (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev12:5\">Lev 12:5</a>).</em></p>\n<h3>Mourning</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen50:10\">GEN 50:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam31:13\">1SA 31:13</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr10:12\">1CH 10:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job2:13\">JOB 2:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek3:15\">EZK 3:15</a></p>\n<h2>The Feast of Weeks</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut16:9-Deut16:10\">DEU 16:9–16:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:22\">EXO 34:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:15-Lev23:21\">LEV 23:15–23:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num28:26-Num28:31\">NUM 28:26–28:31</a></p>\n<h2>Feasts lasting seven days</h2>\n<h3>Wedding feasts</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen29:27\">GEN 29:27</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg14:10-Judg14:12\">JDG 14:10–14:12</a></p>\n<h3>The Feast of Unleavened Bread</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:18\">EXO 34:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:5-Lev23:8\">LEV 23:5–23:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr30:21-2Chr30:23\">2CH 30:21–30:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr35:17\">2CH 35:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra6:22\">EZR 6:22</a></p>\n<h3>The Feast of Tabernacles</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:34\">LEV 23:34</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:36\">LEV 23:36</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh8:18\">NEH 8:18</a></p>\n<h3>Dedication of the temple</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs8:65\">1KI 8:65</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr7:8-2Chr7:9\">2CH 7:8–7:9</a></p>\n<h2>Daniel's ``weeks''</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan9:24\">DAN 9:24</a></strong> <em>“sevens” may also be translated “weeks”.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan9:25-Dan9:27\">DAN 9:25–9:27</a></p>\n<h2>God promises that times and seasons will always continue</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer5:24\">JER 5:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen8:22\">GEN 8:22</a></p>",
